      <t:profileDesc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
         <t:langUsage><t:language ident="en"/><t:language ident="gez"/></t:langUsage>
         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>A Church service made up of psalms, biblical readings and hymns. This record is the general one to be used when the recension of the
               work cannot be identified.
               Four types of <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</t:foreign> have been identified by <t:bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/DZFI5RB2"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Taft1986Liturgy"/><title level="m">The liturgy of the hours in East and West: the origins of the Divine Office and its meaning for today</title><author><forename>Robert F.</forename><surname>Taft</surname></author><pubPlace>Collegeville, Minn.</pubPlace><publisher>The Liturgical Pr.</publisher><date>1986</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Taft1986Liturgy</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Taft1986Liturgy</note><t:citedRange unit="page">266</t:citedRange></t:bibl>:</t:p>
            <t:p> 
               <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2230Saatat">Saʿātāt
                                                  za-gǝbṣ</t:ref>: the Coptic <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</t:foreign>;</t:p>
            <t:p> 
               <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3575Mashaf">Maṣḥafa
                                                  saʿātāt</t:ref>: the <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</t:foreign> of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4709Giyorgis">Giyorgis of Saglā</t:persName>, 
               which replaced the <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2230Saatat">Saʿātāt
                                                  za-gǝbṣ</t:ref>:  and is presently in use in Ethiopia and Eritrea;</t:p>
            <t:p>
               <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3576Saatat">Maṣḥafa
                                                  saʿātāt</t:ref>:  a <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</t:foreign> that includes the entire Psalter in the daily pensum;</t:p>
            <t:p>
               <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3577GizeS">Gize ṣalot</t:ref>: a cursus of prayers which is not really a <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Saʿātāt</t:foreign>, but a <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Gize ṣalot</t:foreign> for hermits and recluses.</t:p>
         </t:abstract>
